nodes.bodyText:
If an interface inherits the same superinterface more than once somewhere in its hierarchy the HashSet will save some native calls.
example:
interface Y extends X {void m() {}}
interface Z extends X, Y {}

X will only be searched once. this example is trivial but if X had many superinterfaces it would show an impact.

